peregrine
Class StructReader

java.lang.Object
  peregrine.StructReader
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<StructReader>, ByteReadable
public class StructReader
extends java.lang.Object
implements ByteReadable, java.lang.Comparable<StructReader>

API for dealing with complex data structures as high level types. All main byte manipulation in peregrine is centered around StructReader and StructWriter. A sibling class StructReaders provides API around easily accessing primitives.

We support the following types: 


 byte
 short
 varint
 int
 long
 float
 double
 boolean
 char
 string
 hashcode

See Also:
StructWriter, StructReaders

readBytes

public byte[] readBytes()
Read a byte array and return it. The byte byte array is length prefixed so that this StructReader can hold mulitiple byte arrays.

readBytesFixed

public byte[] readBytesFixed(int size)
Read a fixed width byte array from the stream. The size must be known ahead of time. This can be useful for writing a large number of objects like longs, hashcodes (8 bytes), etc which are all fixed without having to store the length prefix which would yield overhead.

isReadable

public boolean isReadable()

Return true if the struct is currently readable and there is data ready to be returned. Every read call increments the readerIndex and once readerIndex = writerIndex then this StructReader is no longer readable.

This can be used in loops where you want to keep reading from the StructReader like an enumeration.
